webserver: piece of software designed to accept incoming web requests
example:http://www.google.com , indicates that we are sending:

GET/HTTP/1.1  (here '/' indicates the path. here it is home page)
HOSt:www.google.com

different http verbs:
	GET:retrieve something (example: retrieving google page)
	POST:receive data and use it.(it may create a new item. eg:data can b a piece of json)
	PUT: make sure something is der.(may create if it is not der. if it is der it will update)
	DELETE:remove something


Rest principals:
REST is stateless
